{"lemma":"رَبَضَ","slug":"رَبَضَ","root":"ر.ب.ض","root_slug":"ر-ب-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14485"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lie down, to squat (said of animals)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lurk, to be in position"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to park, to anchor"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put to lie down"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wife"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outskirts, precincts, suburb"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place where animals lie down or lurk"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew רבץ (raváts)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14485","headword_ar":"رَبَضَ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuwDN","text_ar":"رُبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboDN","text_ar":"رَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboDapN","text_ar":"رَبْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [the last an inf. n. of un.,] said of the sheep and goat, (S, A, Mgh, K,) and of the gazelle, (S, A,) and of the ox-kind, and the horse, (S,) or beast, (Msb,) and of the dog, (S, A,) [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lay down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid himself down, upon his breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraka","text_ar":"بَرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a camel, (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"javama","text_ar":"جَثَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a bird, (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasa","text_ar":"جَلَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man. (Mgh.) Said of a man, it means [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lay down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sat upon his knees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it may also mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sat upon his thighs and his buttocks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 172.) [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stationary, like an animal lying upon its breast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is shown by what here follows: whence a signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aDa","text_ar":"رَبَّضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.] The saying of Mohammad to Ed- Dahhák, when he sent him to his people,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA","text_ar":"اـِذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotahumo faA@robiDo fiY daArihimo ZaboyFA","text_ar":"اَتَيْتَهُمْ فَا@رْبِضْ فِى دَارِهِمْ ظَبْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When thou comest to them, remain in their abode in security,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without fear, like the gazelle"},{"kind":"text","text":"in his covert: (IAar, ISd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trust them not, but be vigilant, like a wild animal, ready to spring up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for thou wilt be in the midst of the unbelievers; (Az, ISd, K; *) so, if anything induce in thee suspicion, thou mayest flee from them like the gazelle: (Az, ISd, TA:) accord. to each interpretation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZbyA","text_ar":"ظبيا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the accus. case as a denotative of state; the subst. being put in the place of the act. part. n., as though for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataZab~iyFA","text_ar":"مَتَظَبِّيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former of the two explanations is said to be the more agreeable with the circumstances of the case. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa AlA^asadu EalaY fariysatihi","text_ar":"رَبَضَ الاَسَدُ عَلَى فَرِيسَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqironu EalaY","text_ar":"القِرْنُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qironihi","text_ar":"قِرْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion laid himself down upon his breast"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraka","text_ar":"بَرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on his prey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the adversary on his adversary."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a beast)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodged, and abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became heavy, and slept, stretched upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa Eani Alganami","text_ar":"رَبَضَ عَنِ الغَنَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuwDN","text_ar":"رُبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a ram)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstained from tupping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covering the ewes, and avoided it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being fatigued:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was unable to cover them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) one does not say, of a ram,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jafara","text_ar":"جَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) You say also of a ewe when she is pregnant,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado rubiDa EanohaA","text_ar":"قَدْ رُبِضَ عَنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn- 'Abbád, A.) And you say of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa Eano maEaAliY AlA^umuwri","text_ar":"رَبَضَ عَنْ مَعَالِى الاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abstained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held back, from seeking the means of acquiring eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa","text_ar":"رَبَضَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayolu","text_ar":"اللَّيْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night cast its darkness"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"(expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY bnafosihi","text_ar":"اَلْقَى بنَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDahu","text_ar":"رَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, O, K,) but the latter aor. was afterwards rejected by IAar, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He betook himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired, to him for lodging, covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDatohu","text_ar":"رَبَضَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", and IAar is related to have said"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, but afterwards to have retracted it, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a wife, or sister, or other woman,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertook,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"managed, his affairs, and gave him lodging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she was to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though she were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaD","text_ar":"رَبَض"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abawotuhu","text_ar":"اَبَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I was to him a father, ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amamotuhu","text_ar":"اَمَمْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I was to him a mother. ” (A, TA.) [The aor. occurs in the K, in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobiDu zawojahaA","text_ar":"تَرْبِضُ زَوْجَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the TA:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1012},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turab~iDu","text_ar":"تُرَبِّضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobuDu","text_ar":"تَرْبُضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus also the aor. is written in a copy of the A.]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","Mgh","TA","IAar","ISd","Az","O"]}]}}